credit: NETFLIX

The hunt for the next 007 has officially begun, with Amazon MGM Studios confirming that auditions to find Daniel Craig's successor are actively underway. To tackle the monumental task of casting the next James Bond, the studio has enlisted the expertise of veteran casting director Nina Gold. Known for shaping massive franchise landscapes, Gold’s impressive resume includes populating the world of Westeros for _Game of Thrones_, casting _The Crown_, and finding the new generation of heroes for the _Star Wars_ sequel trilogy.  
  
“The search for the next James Bond is underway,” Amazon MGM Studios said in a statement. “While we don’t plan to comment on specific details during the casting process, we’re excited to share more news with 007 fans as soon as the time is right.”